  "class": "vulnerability",
  "metadata": {
    "title": "non-atomic xattr replace operation (moderate)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2014-9710",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2014-9710",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: The Btrfs implementation in the Linux kernel before 3.19 does not ensure that the visible xattr state is consistent with a requested replacement, which allows local users to bypass intended ACL settings and gain privileges via standard filesystem operations (1) during an xattr-replacement time window, related to a race condition, or (2) after an xattr-replacement attempt that fails because the data does not fit. \n            STATEMENT: This issue does not affect the versions of the kernel package as shipped with\nRed Hat Enterprise Linux 5 and Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2.\n\nThis issue affects the version of Linux kernel as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 and 7. Future kernel updates for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7 may address this issue.\n\nGiven the Moderate impact and the fact that BRTFS file system is no longer Technology preview in Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 this issue is not currently planned to be addressed in future releases of Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.",
